\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/c63ed898ba9acf1ecf390e14d5f7957b?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' /></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/katerila\" class=\"reviewer-name\">katerila</a> le <span class=\"review-date\">février 18, 2020</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\">Love this plugin but something that drives me crazy is how tedious it is to fix readability issues. For example, when you press the \"eye\" icon to highlight all the sentences that are longer than 20 words, as soon as you edit 1 sentence, the highlighting disappears. So then you have to scroll back down and press the \"eye\" icon again to turn on the highlighting. \n\nIf you have 30 sentences to edit, that\'s scrolling up and down 60 times and re-pressing the \"eye\" icon 30 times to toggle the highlight on again after each edit!!!! Why can\'t the highlighting just stay on until I turn it off? Still waiting and waiting for an update that will fix this...</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Amazing helper</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 sur 5 étoiles\" data-title-template=\"%s sur 5 étoiles\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Par <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/sandramaj\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/bfe8839567a95dd8e2bf1e5c3289a460?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avata